# Files under docs/, skills/, and templates/ are copied INTO a consuming project,
# where no `templates/` directory exists — templates/CLAUDE.md lands as CLAUDE.md,
# templates/technical-reference.md as technical-reference.md, and so on. A
# `templates/...` path reference therefore points at nothing once distributed.
# (The `Based on .../blob/XXXXXXX/templates/...` URLs are source-repo links, not
# local paths, and are not backtick-quoted, so they do not match.)
reason=配布される文書がローカルパスとして `templates/...` を参照している。導入先に templates/ は存在しない（配布先での実パスを書く）
pattern=`templates/
glob=docs/**,skills/**,templates/**
